item.title: Does a muffler add horsepower?
item.description: Everything that comes before the muffler, where the pressure is greatest and performance potential is highest, will remain tight and congested. MagnaFlow, an aftermarket exhaust manufacturer, says that its customers can expect horsepower gains of around 10 percent (which is a pretty commonly-quoted figure). Does muffler reduce horsepower? item.title: What is a purple noise?
item.description: Purple noise is a variant of white noise. Purple noise is white noise (a mix of all audible frequencies) that has been filtered so that rather than having an equal representation of all frequencies, the higher frequencies are represented more than the lower ones. Is there purple noise? Blue noise is essentially the inverse of pink noise, with its amplitude increasing by 3dB per octave (the amplitude is proportional to f); and violet noise is the inverse of brown noise, with a rising response of 6dB per octave (amplitude is proportional to f squared).

item.description: An artist has pledged to paint portraits of every single resident in Britain’s smallest city, having already spent 10 years on the project.
